e astrophysical energy range. An upper limit for\nthe 128Ba(g,a)124Xe stellar rate was inferred from our measurement. The impact\nof this rate was studied in two different models for core-collapse supernova\nexplosions of 25 solar mass stars. A significant contribution to the 124Xe\nabundance via this reaction path would only be possible when the rate was\nincreased above the previous standard value. Since the experimental data rule\nthis out, they also demonstrate the closure of this production path.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Sep 2016 07:07:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-14"}
